CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 23, 1954, pg. 15., reads: "Vice President Richard M. Nixon swung himself around with the crowd during his busy visit in Pittsburgh Tuesday....Upper right: Vice President and wife turn from Secret Service men to greet admirers. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Crowd greeting Richard Nixon and Pat Nixon on airport tarmac with American Airlines airplane "Flagship Lake Michigan" in background
